05:04.137 --> 05:06.347
Paula, be totally honest.

05:06.431 --> 05:09.434
Does this suit say,
"Hey, Nathaniel, I'm a lot like you,

05:09.517 --> 05:11.519
a successful power player
who deserves respect

05:11.602 --> 05:14.188
and, at least,
some important responsibilities," hmm?

05:14.272 --> 05:16.774
Yeah, you know,
it says something more like,

05:16.858 --> 05:19.110
"irregular, 30 percent off,
the Suit Barn."

05:20.028 --> 05:21.154
Maybe not that honest.

05:21.237 --> 05:25.366
No, doofus.
That's what it says on your tag.

05:25.450 --> 05:28.119
-Oh! Oh! Oh! Good call!
-Yeah.

05:28.202 --> 05:32.415
-Are there any more?
-Yeah, no, you're... you're... great.

05:34.375 --> 05:38.546
Hey, there. Wow, you have
the most intense look on your face.

05:40.381 --> 05:42.633
I'm excited for your other looks,
whenever those get going.

05:45.303 --> 05:48.473
Wow, so you found
Rebecca's treadmill desk.

05:48.556 --> 05:51.350
Yes, took maintenance a while
to get out the hot dog smell.

05:51.434 --> 05:54.395
Well, you know Rebecca.
She loves to jog and dog.

05:54.479 --> 05:58.357
-Darryl, what can I do for you?
-The question is, "What can <i>I</i> do for <i>you</i>?"

05:58.441 --> 06:00.526
Because I get it.
You're now the number one.

06:00.610 --> 06:04.864
I'm the number two, dangling under you,
ready to drop in, make a splash.

06:04.947 --> 06:06.449
Darryl, stop.

06:06.532 --> 06:10.369
So, you're not craving a number two?
There's no rumblings for a deuce?

06:10.453 --> 06:11.788
No.

06:12.872 --> 06:16.292
Cool, cool. Well, I'm not gonna push it.
I'm just gonna go back one out.

06:16.375 --> 06:19.253
I mean, I'm just gonna back out.

06:23.800 --> 06:24.884
[candy clattering]

06:27.804 --> 06:28.638
Uh-oh.

06:29.847 --> 06:33.017
You're not even separating out
the buttered popcorn flavored ones.

06:33.976 --> 06:37.188
-Didn't go well, huh?
-What? No, it went great.

06:37.271 --> 06:40.149
Yeah, I mean, he doesn't have a lot
for me now, but I know he will soon.

06:40.233 --> 06:43.861
Absolutely. It's all gonna change
once he gets that big client.

06:43.945 --> 06:46.781
That what? What client?

06:46.864 --> 06:49.283
You know, that huge client
that he used to rep in the LA office,

06:49.367 --> 06:51.327
and his dad said he could
also represent them here.

06:52.411 --> 06:58.459
Oh, oh! Yeah, yeah, yeah. The big client.
True. I thought you said the "pig" client.

06:58.543 --> 07:03.005
You don't know about them?
The pork-processing place out in Duarte?

07:03.089 --> 07:05.842
Oh, you've gotta check that out.
But you said the "big" client.

07:05.925 --> 07:09.137
That's the one... That's the one that has
the weird name that's hard to pronounce.

07:09.220 --> 07:11.848
How do-- How do you say it?
Just off the top of your head.

07:11.931 --> 07:15.017
-Say it. Just say it.
-Peterson Car Sales?

07:15.101 --> 07:17.937
Mm, close, but it's actually "Petterson."

07:18.020 --> 07:21.482
It's Petterson Car Sales, yeah.
That's the correct pronunciation.

07:21.566 --> 07:25.611
Anyway, over and out.
I've got a lot of work to do.

07:31.826 --> 07:34.704
Oh! You found my old hot dog cooker.

07:35.413 --> 07:38.040
Pop the cover off, set it to 3.4 MPH,

07:38.124 --> 07:39.959
slide some Ball Park fatties
on those rollers--

07:40.042 --> 07:43.379
-Cooks up real nice.
-[exhales]

07:43.463 --> 07:45.506
Yeah. What are you doing to yourself?

07:45.590 --> 07:47.175
High interval impact training.

07:47.258 --> 07:50.845
It's intense periodic exertion,
which activates your fight or flight.

07:50.928 --> 07:54.765
It's not a real workout unless your body
is convinced it's being chased by a lion.

07:54.849 --> 07:56.267
Mm, that sounds factual.

07:56.350 --> 07:59.645
So, listen, I wanted to let you know
I'm heading out a little early today.

07:59.729 --> 08:02.482
I have some unused vacation days,
and you can fact-check that with Karen.

08:02.565 --> 08:04.233
Okay. Where you going?

08:04.317 --> 08:07.778
You and Flip Flop going on
a romantic weekend at a Sandals Resort?

08:07.862 --> 08:08.863
[chuckles]
"Sandals."

08:08.946 --> 08:11.908
That was really good. It's a little sad
no one else was around to hear that.

08:11.991 --> 08:14.660
I don't know. I might say it again later.
Seriously, where you going?

08:14.744 --> 08:16.954
We are going to a family bar mitzvah.

08:17.038 --> 08:19.749
So, he is going to meet
the entire Garfinkel clan.

08:19.832 --> 08:23.085
That's my mom's side of the family.
It will be wonderful.

08:23.169 --> 08:25.254
All right. If you say so.

08:25.338 --> 08:27.840
I do say so because
he is the man of my dreams.

08:27.924 --> 08:29.800
You know, you say that a lot.

08:29.884 --> 08:33.346
I've never heard anyone else use the term
"man of my dreams" before you.

08:33.429 --> 08:35.389
Sounds like something
a super secure person says.

08:35.473 --> 08:38.809
Uh, well, you don't know us
and you don't know me.

08:38.893 --> 08:40.186
And you don't know us, so...

08:40.269 --> 08:42.855
Well, you are gonna miss
something great around here.

08:42.939 --> 08:48.277
My father is just about to give us
a huge client. Massive.

08:48.361 --> 08:50.321
Just waiting
for the final go-ahead from him.

08:50.404 --> 08:53.324
So, go have fun.
I'll be here, being awesome.

08:54.575 --> 08:58.162
Oh, hey, on your way out, can you just
give me a roar? A loud, fast roar?

08:58.246 --> 09:02.041
Doesn't have to be a lion. It can be like
a howler monkey or something like that.

09:02.124 --> 09:04.544
Anything, really. Just a predator.

09:04.627 --> 09:07.213
A land-based predator would be--
Never mind.

09:07.296 --> 09:09.465
Have a great weekend.

09:09.549 --> 09:12.343
-It's a family event. That's a big step.
-Yeah.

09:13.594 --> 09:16.514
Almost as big as when you announced
your relationship status on Waze,

09:16.597 --> 09:18.474
which I didn't even know was a thing.

09:18.558 --> 09:21.352
Well, when it feels this great,
you want everyone to know.

09:22.603 --> 09:23.688
Everyone?

09:34.532 --> 09:35.950
Thank you for texting me back.

09:36.033 --> 09:38.411
I, um, used up my data plan

09:38.494 --> 09:41.956
sending you sad Bitmojis
and <i>Golden Girls</i> gifs.

09:42.039 --> 09:45.585
Jifs? Is it gifs or jifs?
Never mind, it's not your job to tell me.

09:45.668 --> 09:47.461
Yeah, uh...

09:47.545 --> 09:51.215
I had to take a few days
once I heard about you and Josh.

09:51.299 --> 09:53.467
I wanted to make sure you're okay.

09:53.551 --> 09:57.346
It's not my favorite thing,
you guys being a couple...

09:57.430 --> 09:58.681
but I'm okay.

09:58.764 --> 10:01.309
And are we okay?
The answer doesn't have to be "yes."

10:01.392 --> 10:04.812
Good because the answer is "eh."

10:04.895 --> 10:06.647
Totally get it.

10:06.731 --> 10:08.649
But don't worry about me, really.

10:08.733 --> 10:10.568
If you need to worry about someone,
worry about yourself.

10:10.651 --> 10:12.069
Me, why?

10:12.153 --> 10:15.448
Don't you see that Josh
is, like, all over the place and lost?

10:15.531 --> 10:17.408
But that was before.

10:17.491 --> 10:19.452
And I saw from a post
you shared on OpenTable

10:19.535 --> 10:21.203
that you're taking him home
to see your family.

10:22.079 --> 10:24.957
I know your relationship
with your mom is kinda tough.

10:25.041 --> 10:27.710
Yeah, but now I have Josh.
So, you know, it won't bother me.

10:29.045 --> 10:30.630
Love protects you.

10:30.713 --> 10:31.797
[scoffs]

10:31.881 --> 10:33.966
So, the things that used
to annoy me about going home

10:34.050 --> 10:35.968
won't annoy me anymore.

10:36.052 --> 10:41.349
You know? Josh is like a blankie,
a suit of armor, or a bulletproof vest.

10:41.432 --> 10:44.894
Honey, just because Josh Chan
owns all those things

10:44.977 --> 10:47.229
doesn't mean he <i>is</i> all those things.

10:47.313 --> 10:48.814
He's not magic.

10:48.898 --> 10:51.525
It's like magic, FB,
when Rebecca and I are together.

10:51.609 --> 10:54.153
Yeah, I read about it on your post
on Draw Something.

10:54.236 --> 10:56.113
-[bird twitters]
-Oh! Shh, shh!

10:57.782 --> 11:01.035
-Nope. Sorry, go on.
-[sighs]

11:01.118 --> 11:04.246
This family weekend is really important,
and I don't want to screw it up.

11:04.330 --> 11:05.915
You know Rebecca's mother doesn't like me.

11:05.998 --> 11:10.002
