28:01.096 --> 28:04.057
<i>♪ This DJ is terrific</i>
<i>Remember that we suffered ♪</i>

28:04.140 --> 28:06.059
My grandma's a survivor. <i>♪ Remember that she suffered ♪</i>

28:08.144 --> 28:11.272
[vocalizing]

28:11.356 --> 28:14.401
[continues vocalizing]

28:14.484 --> 28:20.990
[inhales deeply, continues vocalizing]

28:21.074 --> 28:24.744
<i>♪ The sweet and the bitter</i>
<i>Remember that we suffered ♪</i>

28:24.828 --> 28:27.831
<i>♪ Streisand and Hitler</i>
<i>Remember that we suffered ♪</i>

28:27.914 --> 28:31.584
<i>♪ Spielberg and Hitler</i>
<i>Remember that we suffered ♪</i>

28:31.668 --> 28:34.796
<i>♪ Have we mentioned Hitler?</i>
<i>I'm just saying that we suffered ♪</i>

28:34.879 --> 28:36.881
When I say "we," you say "suffered."

28:36.965 --> 28:38.550
-We! We!
-Suffered! Suffered!

28:38.633 --> 28:39.968
I can't hear you!

28:40.051 --> 28:42.387
<i>♪ Remember that we suffered, hey! ♪</i>

28:42.470 --> 28:44.931
[people cheering, clapping]

28:46.391 --> 28:49.811
-Okay, so... see what I mean?
-I don't know, Rebecca.

28:49.894 --> 28:53.189
It seems like the only person
who's miserable here is you.

29:06.995 --> 29:08.830
[snickering]

29:10.749 --> 29:12.125
What the hell!

29:14.794 --> 29:18.506
Darryl. I can see you.
There are slats here.

29:19.632 --> 29:22.135
Have you ever hidden before?
Do you know what hiding is?

29:23.553 --> 29:27.348
If you stocked these cabinets with candy
when you knew I had it removed,

29:27.432 --> 29:30.143
that's gonna be a very big problem for us.

29:30.226 --> 29:32.771
Hmm? Tell me you didn't do this, Darryl.

29:35.648 --> 29:36.775
Tell me the truth.

29:37.650 --> 29:39.652
You want to know the truth?

29:39.736 --> 29:42.030
Oh, I'll tell you truth. The truth is...

29:42.113 --> 29:43.198
I did it!

29:45.366 --> 29:48.912
It was me. I got the Snickers.

29:51.873 --> 29:53.500
And I got the Skittles.

29:55.752 --> 29:57.587
I got the Milk Duds.

29:58.755 --> 30:00.799
I got the Toblerone.

30:00.882 --> 30:03.384
And I brought gummy vitamins.

30:03.468 --> 30:04.969
[all groan]

30:05.804 --> 30:08.431
You can take our candy...

30:09.557 --> 30:14.103
but you can never take our candy!

30:14.187 --> 30:15.772
What do you have to say to that?

30:16.815 --> 30:19.442
Well, I say
you're all a bunch of children.

30:19.526 --> 30:20.985
Now, go back to work!

30:28.576 --> 30:31.746
Rebecca! What are you doing
sitting by yourself?

30:31.830 --> 30:33.331
Are you not having fun?

30:33.414 --> 30:36.543
No, I'm not having fun.
My boyfriend is, though.

30:36.626 --> 30:39.379
Yeah, he's making everyone really happy.
He loves it here.

30:39.462 --> 30:41.214
And that's not what you wanted?

30:41.297 --> 30:45.385
No! I wanted him to see
how unhappy everything makes me

30:45.468 --> 30:48.221
and that I'm right
and that everyone here is miserable.

30:48.304 --> 30:50.056
Why is everyone here miserable?

30:50.139 --> 30:52.559
Uh, I don't know.
Maybe because Jewish people's DNA

30:52.642 --> 30:55.645
is literally imprinted
with our past trauma?

30:55.728 --> 30:58.273
It's something called epigenetics.
Look it up.

30:58.356 --> 30:59.691
Hey, don't be condescending.

30:59.774 --> 31:02.694
You think you're the only person
who reads <i>Tablet Magazine </i>on Twitter?

31:03.486 --> 31:08.867
Rebecca, our people is not responsible
for your life. You are.

31:11.035 --> 31:16.541
Maybe. I don't know. I just...
I hate it here. I hate all this stuff.

31:17.417 --> 31:22.505
Oh, well, this stuff, this town,
these people... they're you.

31:22.589 --> 31:24.674
And if you hate that stuff,
you hate yourself.

31:24.757 --> 31:26.342
Oy, here you go.

31:26.426 --> 31:27.844
And if you hate yourself,

31:27.927 --> 31:30.805
it doesn't matter
how great your boyfriend is.

31:30.889 --> 31:32.765
You'll always be unhappy.

31:35.518 --> 31:37.395
But I thought that when you loved someone,

31:37.478 --> 31:40.982
it just fixed everything
and made your life great.

31:41.065 --> 31:43.443
That's a lot to put on a human being.

31:43.526 --> 31:46.404
Yeah, but he's not a human being.
He's Josh Chan.

31:48.239 --> 31:51.409
When we were kids,
he made me feel so happy. And...

31:52.410 --> 31:56.247
I guess I just thought
that if I could get back to that place,

31:56.331 --> 31:59.876
that my life would magically be okay. That's not love, my dear.
It's fantasy. It's not real.

32:09.636 --> 32:12.263
-[typing]
-Um...

32:12.347 --> 32:15.141
-Your father's on line one.
-Close the door.

32:15.224 --> 32:17.226
-[door closes]
-[takes deep breath]

32:17.310 --> 32:18.144
[phone beeps]

32:18.227 --> 32:22.357
Pops! Papa! Papa-doodle-doo!
What's the word?

32:24.067 --> 32:26.277
We're all gearing up
to get going on Peterson,

32:26.361 --> 32:29.322
so once we lock them in,
we can hit the ground running.

32:31.199 --> 32:32.158
Uh-huh.

32:33.451 --> 32:36.663
Uh-huh, uh-huh.
Yep, yep. Yeah, yeah, yeah.

32:36.746 --> 32:38.998
Okay, so that's a "no."
That's fine. I hear you.

32:39.082 --> 32:41.876
Yeah, I know. You gotta earn it.
Nothing gets handed to you.

32:41.960 --> 32:44.295
I love that. That's how we do. "Once you stop improving,
you start losing."

32:46.798 --> 32:49.759
I know. I hear you, sir.
I love that saying. Mm-hmm.

32:49.842 --> 32:51.552
-Okay. Bye-bye.
-[phone beeps]

32:55.431 --> 32:58.226
That's it. I've had it.
I can't take it anymore.

32:58.309 --> 33:00.812
I'm responsible
for that jerk being in our office,

33:00.895 --> 33:04.107
so I should be the one
to stand up to him. [exhales]

33:13.241 --> 33:14.242
What's going on?

33:14.325 --> 33:18.371
Gotta burn the calories.
Gotta work hard.

33:18.454 --> 33:21.165
I had a brief lapse in judgment
with that stupid candy!

33:21.249 --> 33:23.167
But it's okay. I'll just burn it off.

33:23.251 --> 33:26.212
I gotta burn the mistakes.
I mean, burn the calories.

33:26.295 --> 33:28.548
Always improving, never a loser.

33:28.631 --> 33:31.050
Always improving, never a loser.

33:32.051 --> 33:34.095
No, no! Wait a minute! Wait a minute!
I don't think that's safe!

33:34.178 --> 33:35.596
-[groans]
-[gasps]

33:35.680 --> 33:37.682
Nathaniel, are you okay?

33:37.765 --> 33:40.393
[panting]

33:40.476 --> 33:42.395
I'm so sad.

33:42.478 --> 33:45.481
[crying]

33:55.575 --> 33:56.659
Are you okay?

33:58.119 --> 34:02.331
Yeah, I'm fine.
They gave me a temporary tooth.

34:04.333 --> 34:09.047
I'm sorry you had to see that, Darryl.
That was... not professional.

34:09.130 --> 34:13.760
-You know, it's okay to be upset.
-No, it's not. It's weak.

34:15.720 --> 34:17.722
Does this have something to do
with your dad?

34:19.432 --> 34:20.641
Did he not give you the account?

34:22.101 --> 34:23.853
Oh...

34:23.936 --> 34:28.357
You know, my dad is a real jerk too.
Oh! He used to yell at me all the time.

34:28.441 --> 34:30.943
He used to call me
an emasculated sock puppet.

34:31.027 --> 34:33.946
Oh! That's where that's from.

34:34.864 --> 34:36.824
I'm gonna bury that again.

34:36.908 --> 34:37.909
Hold on.

34:40.369 --> 34:42.163
Done. Ha!

34:42.246 --> 34:44.123
Hey, you know what?

34:44.207 --> 34:46.459
You're doing really well, Nathaniel.

34:46.542 --> 34:49.587
No, I see how hard you work,
how talented you are,

34:49.670 --> 34:51.255
how little food you eat. You're a very disciplined young man,

34:53.925 --> 34:56.302
and you don't need your dad
to tell you that.

34:56.385 --> 34:59.764
You have to know that for yourself.

35:02.934 --> 35:04.644
I've been kind of a jerk to you, Darryl.

35:06.229 --> 35:09.315
And I'm gonna pay to have the tooth blood
cleaned out of your car.

35:09.398 --> 35:10.691
Well, thank you.

35:12.693 --> 35:16.447
You're a good kid. Apology accepted.

35:16.531 --> 35:17.865
Well, I didn't apologize.

35:17.949 --> 35:20.576
Well, you kinda did.
I mean, basically, you did.

35:20.660 --> 35:22.161
Nope. Never happened.

35:29.794 --> 35:32.880
Babe, I'm sorry things didn't work out
the way you wanted.

35:32.964 --> 35:36.134
I was trying really hard, but I feel
like you wanted something from me,

35:36.217 --> 35:37.927
and I didn't give it to you.

35:38.010 --> 35:40.429
No, you were fine.
It's-- It's honestly all fine.

35:40.513 --> 35:41.597
Let's just go home.

35:43.182 --> 35:45.977
-Are you mad at me?
-No, no, I'm not mad.

35:46.060 --> 35:48.354
I just don't want to talk about it. Um...

35:49.689 --> 35:51.858
I left something in the bathroom.
I'll be right back.

35:51.941 --> 35:55.653
End of trip selfie?
#shalommeansbothhelloandgoodbye.

35:55.736 --> 35:57.655
No, I'm-- I'm good. Thanks.

36:01.200 --> 36:02.994
[door opens, closes]

36:03.077 --> 36:06.038
I'm gonna wrap this lox up
so you have something to eat on the plane.

36:06.122 --> 36:07.707
Now, I know it may not be enough,

36:07.790 --> 36:10.960
but those nitwits at the deli
were running short and I...

36:11.043 --> 36:12.128
Josh...

36:12.211 --> 36:14.005
Huh? What?

36:14.088 --> 36:15.673
What's wrong?

36:16.507 --> 36:18.176
Uh, it's just...

36:21.095 --> 36:23.389
Rebecca seems like she's mad at me.

36:23.472 --> 36:25.975
And I wanted this weekend
to bring us together,

36:26.058 --> 36:28.269
but it feels like she's pulling away.

36:28.352 --> 36:31.355
And you have no idea how much
this relationship means to me.

36:31.439 --> 36:34.650
I told everyone about it.
It can't fall apart now. Well, it won't...
because I won't let that happen.

36:38.029 --> 36:39.363
You won't?

36:39.447 --> 36:44.660
No, I actually think you and Rebecca
are pretty wonderful together.

36:44.744 --> 36:47.496
You soften some of her sharp edges,
thank God.

36:47.580 --> 36:50.249
[chuckles]
Wow.

36:50.333 --> 36:52.752
Thanks, Naomi.
That's nice of you to say.

36:53.753 --> 36:55.338
But what do I do now?

36:55.421 --> 36:58.341
Joshua, I am your Jewish mother now,

36:58.424 --> 37:01.385
and there are two things
I will always have.

37:01.469 --> 37:03.346
Indigestion and all the answers.

37:03.930 --> 37:04.764
[chuckles]

37:04.847 --> 37:07.725
So, just listen to me
and do exactly as I say.

37:22.073 --> 37:23.199
You know what?

37:24.158 --> 37:26.202
I do eat a bit too much candy.

37:26.285 --> 37:30.581
My liver is basically 40 percent
high fructose corn syrup. [chuckles]

37:30.665 --> 37:31.791
Well, good choice.

37:32.750 --> 37:35.378
You know, I was thinking, Darryl--
[clears throat] I'm so slammed.

37:35.461 --> 37:38.589
Maybe you would like to take over
the Crestfield account?

37:38.673 --> 37:42.510
The what? That's...
That's, like, our biggest client.

37:42.593 --> 37:45.429
Yeah, and I need a co-pilot.

37:47.098 --> 37:50.726
Co-pilot Darryl C. Whitefeather
reporting for duty, sir.

37:52.645 --> 37:56.941
Maya, could you please get that?
I'm very busy. Got a ton of work to do.

37:58.567 --> 38:00.027
Your office is that way.

38:04.699 --> 38:07.076
I don't know.
I've been giving it a lot of thought.

38:07.159 --> 38:10.246
And maybe Rabbi Shari's right.

38:11.247 --> 38:12.915
About me not loving myself.

38:12.999 --> 38:14.292
You know, maybe there's...

38:15.459 --> 38:18.129
there's something else
at the core of my unhappiness

38:18.212 --> 38:19.588
that I didn't realize.

38:22.925 --> 38:24.760
I'm sorry, what did you say?

38:24.844 --> 38:30.683
Well, she said that I wouldn't find
my answers in another person, and...

38:30.766 --> 38:33.102
I don't know.
That's starting to make a lot of sense.

38:35.688 --> 38:38.774
[whistling]

38:40.401 --> 38:41.694
Go on.

38:42.445 --> 38:45.531
Well, I moved to West Covina

38:45.614 --> 38:47.908
'cause I thought my problems
would be solved by a boy.

38:49.118 --> 38:54.123
Now, I'm with that boy, and...
I still have the same problems.

38:54.206 --> 38:58.294
So... I don't know.
Maybe it's something else.

38:58.377 --> 39:03.007
And if he is not the answer,

39:03.090 --> 39:06.052
what could it be about?

39:07.053 --> 39:08.220
It could be...

39:10.139 --> 39:11.307
my own issues.

39:13.768 --> 39:15.770
Oh, what's wrong?

39:15.853 --> 39:19.648
Nothing. It's just... I'm...

39:19.732 --> 39:22.902
I'm so... happy.

39:22.985 --> 39:24.779
Oh.

39:24.862 --> 39:27.448
Could you stay a little longer today?

39:28.574 --> 39:32.036
Candace! Cancel my next five appointments!

39:32.119 --> 39:36.957
Rebecca, do you think
that you're finally really ready

39:37.041 --> 39:39.835
to confront your issues?

39:40.669 --> 39:44.673
I think... I think maybe...

39:44.757 --> 39:46.258
Yes. Yes, I am.

39:47.385 --> 39:50.137
[whistling]

39:50.221 --> 39:52.473
-What's that noise?
-Nothing. It doesn't matter.

39:52.556 --> 39:55.267
You were saying
you can't be happy in life

39:55.351 --> 39:57.186
until you're happy with yourself?

39:57.269 --> 40:02.149
Yes, but figuring out what that is,
being happy with myself...

40:03.275 --> 40:06.404
That's a hard and scary road
that I don't know if I want to go down.

40:06.487 --> 40:08.739
-[whistling continues]
-What is that noise?

40:08.823 --> 40:13.160
Don't-Don't-- Stay with me.
Come on. Stay with me.

40:13.244 --> 40:15.329
So, maybe...

40:15.413 --> 40:18.290
maybe I need to just take
some time on my own...

40:19.917 --> 40:20.876
to figure--

40:23.003 --> 40:25.297
-Josh?
-What are you doing here?

40:29.009 --> 40:31.512
The Garfinkel ring. But how did you--?

40:31.595 --> 40:35.141
You told me you pawned it, so I went
to the pawn shop on East Cameron--

40:35.224 --> 40:36.225
Rebecca, stay with me.

40:36.308 --> 40:40.271
You're working on yourself,
you're taking time out to be alone...

40:40.354 --> 40:44.567
Oh, my God, you remembered me
saying that? This is so romantic.

40:46.360 --> 40:50.906
Oh, no! No! No! No!

40:57.329 --> 41:01.041
Oh, my God, this is like a fairy tale.
This is everything I've ever wanted.

41:01.125 --> 41:02.835
[Akopian]
Get up, Josh. Get up.

41:04.253 --> 41:07.173
-Get up, Josh!
-Rebecca Nora Bunch...

41:07.256 --> 41:08.632
-...will...
-No! [gasps]

41:10.176 --> 41:12.219
-...you...
-Wait!

41:13.387 --> 41:15.598
-...marry...
-Please!

41:15.681 --> 41:18.058
-...me?
-Yes!

41:18.142 --> 41:19.226
No!

41:19.310 --> 41:20.686
[groans]

41:28.944 --> 41:31.572
-So, you live in Los Angeles?
-Basically.

41:31.655 --> 41:33.616
-Do you know Jeremy Stein?
-No.

41:33.699 --> 41:36.035
-Do you know Josh Berger?
-No.

41:36.118 --> 41:37.703
-Do you know Sam Goldberg?
-Nope.

41:37.786 --> 41:39.038
-Do you know Sammy Goldberg?
-No.

41:39.121 --> 41:40.915
-Did you go to Camp Nock-A-Mixon?
-No.

41:40.998 --> 41:42.708
-Did you go to Camp Winadu?
-No.

41:43.542 --> 41:47.004
-Have you ever met a Jew before Rebecca?
-No.

41:47.087 --> 41:49.548
Yeah, probably should've started
with that question.
